//////////// decoder

DECODER FROM <mnemonic> INPUT IRRLS<operand akaname>  OUTPUT SR TO <MACROOP_NAME>


//////////// OPERAND NAME
TYPENAME    T_TEMP    aka   T### temporal register,
            T_REG     aka   R### register operand,
            T_MEM_LD  aka   L### load operand
            T_MEM_ST  aka   S### store operand
            T_IMM     aka   I### imm operand


MACROOP <MACROOP_NAME>
      INPUT <TYPE_NAME> <VAR_NAME> ..........
      OUTPUT <TYPE_NAME> <VAR_NAME> ..........
      TEMP   <VAR_NAME> ...............   # in temp case type is not required due to reg operand
      MICROOP <MICROOP_NAME> INPUT <VAR_NAME> ... OUTPUT <VAR_NAME> ...    # INPUT and OUTPUT for microop is required even though there is no input or out
      MICROOP <MICROOP_NAME> INPUT <VAR_NAME> ... OUTPUT <VAR_NAME> ...
MACROOP_END
//////////////////// eventhough you do not need input/output in microop you must specify INPUT/OUTPUT keyword


//////////// MICROOP LANGUAGE
TYPENAME   TREG ### temporal register,
            REG ### register,
            MEM ### memory

MICROOP <MACROOP_NAME>
    INPUT  <TYPE_NAME> <VAR_NAME> ..........
    OUTPUT <TYPE_NAME> <VAR_NAME> ..........
MICROOP_END